cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.AL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a distributed online algorithm for workload re-embedding. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses the benefits of dynamically adjusting network resources to improve performance. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with reconfigurable systems and the tradeoff between benefits and costs. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper studies a fundamental model and proposes an algorithm for dynamically collocating communication partners. 
- cs.AL (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper derives a lower bound on the competitive ratio of any online algorithm.
